definition.value: A diarylmethane that is 2-chlorophenyl(phenyl)methane substituted on the methane carbon by a 2-(dimethylamino)ethyl group. Used in the treatment of dry cough, it suppresses the cough reflex by a direct effect on the cough centre in the medulla of the brain.
A racemate comprising of equimolar amounts of (2R,3S)- and (2S,3R)-bifluranol. It is an antiprostatic agent.
